article.headline: UC Irvine 75, New Mexico State 62
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Greg Ethington scored a game-high 19 points to lead UC Irvine to a 75-62 victory over New Mexico State on Tuesday night. Aaron Fitzgerald added 14 points and Ross Schraeder had 12 points for the Anteaters (5-2), who won their fourth consecutive game. Freshman Josh Jenkins came off the bench to score 18 points for the Aggies (3-7), who have lost five straight and seven of eight. Antwan Alexander added 14 points. Irvine made four of its first eight shots to build a 10-0 lead with 3:12 gone. New Mexico State did not score until Byron Davis made a 3-pointer 3:23 into the game. Lawrence's lay-up 25 seconds into the second half narrowed the Aggies' deficit to 43-36, but Fitzgerald and Darren Fells scored four points apiece during an 8-0 run that gave the Anteaters a 51-36 lead with 16:44 to play. Irvine extended its lead to 19 points with 5:27 left. New Mexico State committed 23 turnovers, 13 in the second half.
